<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!--
    Hardened Runtime entitlements for an Electron app destined for
    Developer ID distribution (NOT Mac App Store).

    These three are the minimum for a notarizable Electron app. Each one
    relaxes a specific check that hardened runtime tightens by default:

    - allow-jit: V8 needs to JIT-compile JavaScript at runtime, which
      requires writable+executable memory pages. Without this, V8 crashes
      on launch.

    - allow-unsigned-executable-memory: Electron creates executable pages
      not signed by us (V8 generated code, FFI thunks). Without this, the
      kernel kills the process.

    - disable-library-validation: We load native modules (better-sqlite3)
      and Electron's Helper bundles. Their code signatures aren't issued
      by the same Team ID as our app's main signature. Without this, the
      loader refuses to dlopen them.

    We DELIBERATELY do NOT enable App Sandbox here — that's for Mac App
    Store distribution and would require additional entitlements for
    network, file access etc. Developer ID + hardened runtime gives us
    the "no Gatekeeper trash" outcome without the sandbox restrictions.
  -->
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
  <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
